      "side": 1,
      "message": "Right, the way it works right now is the Title is actually taken from ConsoleGroups. If you look at the HTML template it iterates through one of these structures, but then uses data from both using \"index.\" Having a unified data structure would probably be the cleanest though, and something like what you describe was what I was thinking, the downside is it basically means a deep-copy of config.ConsoleSummaryGroup into this new data structure, which is essentially just config.ConsoleSummaryGroup with []*model.BuilderSummary tacked on at the bottom layer.\n\nBecause the ConsoleSummaryGroup is already mostly ready for rendering, it ends up being a bunch of duplicate code between the proto and this, hence my hesitation to do this initially.",
